modules.description: This module serializes OCaml values into XML elements. It supports primitive types like booleans, integers, floats, characters, strings, and unit, as well as structured data such as tuples, records, and variants. Use it to generate XML representations of typed data structures programmatically.

This module serializes data to XML, converting `Ser.data` structures into formatted XML strings with support for pretty-printing. It handles primitive and structured OCaml types, producing results that capture serialization errors. Use it to generate XML for APIs or config files, leveraging child modules to serialize specific data shapes like records or variants into XML elements.
